The paper deals with robust Principal Components Analysis (PCA), which is a topic in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG, cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of partial knowledge about the column space of the low rank matrix, which involves linear algebra and information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a modified version of the PCP algorithm, which involves numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the problem to time series data, which involves signal processing and statistical inference (cs.SI).
